Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.61,0:00:18.60,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Piercing through the Macro sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.35,0:00:24.31,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,a thunderbolt strikes the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.05,0:00:30.01,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,To awaken us, the young mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.79,0:00:36.73,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,the Light struck
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.87,0:00:41.83,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.07,0:00:48.44,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The brave youths who arise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.71,0:00:52.61,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,and fight to protect their loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:00:57.78,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will set out on their journey\Nas the war rages on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.05,0:01:00.95,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you love me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:06.29,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Slicing through the darkness they fly toward
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.56,0:01:12.50,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,That blue planet that shines in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.50,0:01:17.30,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.71,0:01:23.84,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.46,0:01:36.58,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Major Focker has died in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.69,0:01:42.36,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,The shock of this has pierced the hearts\Nof Claudia and those around her,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.36,0:01:49.93,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,including Hikaru Ichijo, whose injuries\Nprevented him from participating in the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.67,0:01:55.61,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(73,136)}BURST POINT
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.32,0:02:09.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Global!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:14.20,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Low-level flights over urban areas are\Nprohibited except in emergencies!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.20,0:02:16.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Increase altitude and go out\Nover the sea at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.90,0:02:19.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This {\i1}is{\i0} an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:23.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,With 56,000 civilians on board we can't\Nuse the Macross to its full potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.94,0:02:26.88,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Request authorization to let\Nthe civilians disembark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:29.88,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one of those passengers must\Nset foot on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.88,0:02:32.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the decision of\NHigh Command!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.41,0:02:35.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Global, you aren't trying to oppose\Nthat decision, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.42,0:02:36.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not what I'm saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.92,0:02:39.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that our gravity control\Nsystem still isn't perfected,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.92,0:02:42.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and if it were to malfunction...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.46,0:02:44.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.13,0:02:47.99,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you know what would happen\Nif the Macross crashed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:51.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I request authorization to let\Nthe refugees disembark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.63,0:02:54.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do that!\NReconsider, Global!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:03:01.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right for us to be\Nmaking threats like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.34,0:03:03.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Macross is the symbol of the UN Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:09.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If the captain of the Macross were to rebel,\Nthe people would lose all confidence in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.28,0:03:13.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But UN High Command can't\Nafford to make matters any worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.19,0:03:14.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.16,0:03:19.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. But if they do decide\Nto make an example of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.23,0:03:21.20,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take full responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.33,0:03:24.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose that High Command\Nwill change their decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:26.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.14,0:03:28.90,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why have we...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.90,0:03:31.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if High Command refuses\Nauthorization to release the refugees,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:37.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,some autonomous government may intercept\Nour transmission and agree to take them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.41,0:03:39.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly hope they can\Nfind somewhere to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:42.14,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.52,0:03:47.48,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, until we do find somewhere for them to go,\NI'm heading out for a cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.76,0:03:49.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what kind of cake should I have with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.83,0:03:52.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,"Cake," she says...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:54.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,She's really pushing herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.23,0:03:55.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:03:59.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If I lost somebody I loved,\NI'd lose my appetite right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:09.28,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On the cafe terrace, dyed crimson with the sunset,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:13.82,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The fragrance of Turkish coffee fills the air
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:18.52,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Along with a listless tango rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.52,0:04:22.92,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm alone and lonely, but if I dance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:27.90,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A breeze will blow through my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:31.53,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you don't show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.20,0:04:36.77,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder who I'll be dancing with tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.77,0:04:39.11,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Silver Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:41.51,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Red Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.51,0:04:46.38,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're so cold, Shanghai dandy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.38,0:04:51.32,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The smoke from the Gitanes gets in my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.93,0:05:05.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're all better now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.93,0:05:06.90,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.27,0:05:09.49,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if I kept staying in bed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:14.04,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The night makes the gypsy violin cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:12.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,over a few bumps and scrapes\Nlike that, Sempai would...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:18.31,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wine bottle and the two glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.47,0:05:23.22,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I burn for you, and I feel wretched.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.31,0:05:21.65,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how's the plan to get the\Ncivilians off the Macross coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.65,0:05:24.52,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can just find someplace to take them in,\Nwe could carry it out at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.69,0:05:27.41,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm alone and lonely, but if I toast,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.14,0:05:28.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your girlfriend that\Nsings this song, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.77,0:05:30.83,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A breeze will make the small flame dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.36,0:05:30.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Will she leave the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:33.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Minmay said she's staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:36.49,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you don't show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.92,0:05:37.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with her aunt, uncle and cousin, Kaifun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.97,0:05:41.50,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder who I'll be drinking with tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.47,0:05:39.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.66,0:05:40.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaifun will be staying, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:42.84,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Silver Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.74,0:05:45.75,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, being on the surface doesn't\Nmean they'll be any safer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:46.07,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Red Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:51.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And we've developed an Omni-Directional\NBarrier that can cover the whole Macross, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.27,0:05:50.95,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're so cold, Shanghai dandy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:55.78,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The smoke from the Gitanes gets in my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:54.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a lot more reassuring\Nthan the Pinpoint Barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:57.07,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,but it doesn't hold for as long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.32,0:06:04.26,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So if the Zentradi attack\Nus all-out, we'd all die, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:07.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:12.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We already know we're going to lose\Nsomeday, yet we keep on fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.28,0:06:26.51,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:29.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure feel worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.02,0:06:32.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Minmay?\NYou look a little pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.55,0:06:35.85,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, Kaifun.\NI just need to rest for a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.89,0:06:40.73,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay! Hang in there! Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:42.69,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.44,0:06:51.61,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain! I'm receiving an encrypted telegram
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:53.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,from the North American Ontario\NAutonomous Region.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:56.54,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ontario Autonomous Region?\NWhat does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.15,0:07:00.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm decrypting it. "We will take in\Nthe residents of the Macross."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.72,0:07:03.51,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,"Please proceed to this area." Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.75,0:07:05.05,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.56,0:07:11.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Claudia, set a course for the\NOntario region at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.83,0:07:15.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir! Changing course, 1208.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.46,0:07:18.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Destination: Ontario Autonomous Region.\NWe are now underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:31.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! Why would they say\Nwe can't attack the Macross?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.11,0:07:35.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't profess to know what our\Nsuperiors are thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:37.35,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,but the order is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:40.79,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the spy operation is complete,\Nwe are to hold our positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.79,0:07:44.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be joking! The Macross\Nhas returned to its homeworld!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.09,0:07:47.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:50.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to blow it and its homeworld to dust!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.23,0:07:55.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamujin! Kamujin, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.84,0:07:56.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Milia...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.41,0:08:01.48,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we'll have problems\Nunless you stop Kamujin again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.48,0:08:02.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.91,0:08:03.88,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:08.32,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Lap'Lamiz, assign me\Nto be a miclone spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:09.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...? That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:13.75,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would a pilot of your caliber\Nwant to become a miclone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:15.38,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Milia!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.59,0:08:18.65,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I will become a miclone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.80,0:08:28.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've been in hundreds, even thousands, of\Nbattles against the Supervision Army
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.50,0:08:30.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and have never been defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.14,0:08:36.37,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yet now I have lost to a mere miclone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:42.15,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to meet the pilot of that fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:48.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:51.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:51.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\c&HFFFFFF&}Leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.19,0:08:52.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Max, Kakizaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.96,0:08:54.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.56,0:08:57.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We asked Capt. Hayase and\Nshe said you'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.60,0:09:01.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Major Focker's Skull One, right, Leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:04.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, as of today, I'll be taking\Nher up in Sempai's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.34,0:09:09.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He always bragged about how he'd never been\Nshot down, now all that's left of him is this plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.24,0:09:12.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, I've been shot down\Nwho knows how many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.58,0:09:15.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,yet here I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.35,0:09:21.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Leader, have you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.72,0:09:23.69,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they'll be dropping off\Nthe civilians soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.73,0:09:26.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's been settled?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.46,0:09:30.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Ontario Autonomous Region\Nsaid that they'll take them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.83,0:09:33.33,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll make a public announcement\Nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.33,0:09:34.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:40.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Leader, how about we go out on\Nthe town while things are still lively?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.21,0:09:43.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say, sir?\NYou do need to relax once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:46.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.\NTonight, everything's on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.45,0:09:48.25,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Leader for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:51.12,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that that's settled, let's head\Nstraight out to someplace fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.12,0:09:52.65,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Someplace fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:53.38,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:07.40,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get in close to the Macross\Nand hit it with ECM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:09.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,When we do, bring the fleet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.24,0:10:12.64,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But, sir! The big ships don't handle\Nso well in an atmosphere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.64,0:10:18.31,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't start. Rumor has it that the miclones\Nhold dear to this planet of theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.31,0:10:21.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If we get close enough to the surface,\Nthey're as good as ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.28,0:10:25.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it. We'll be disobeyin'\Norders again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.16,0:10:30.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who's afraid to disobey orders would\Nnever make it in the Kamujin Clan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.44,0:10:45.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Multiple unidentified flying objects have entered\Nthe atmosphere and are heading our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:46.97,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.97,0:10:49.64,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And we were just about to reach\Nthe Ontario region.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.64,0:10:50.77,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:53.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let them get us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.18,0:10:55.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hayase, order all pilots to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.68,0:10:56.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:00.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Who had the jumbo sirloin, medium?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.96,0:11:02.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:03.99,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This looks great!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.66,0:11:06.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakizaki, are you really gonna eat all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:09.43,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't, then I'll get the leftovers to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:14.20,intercom paging,,0000,0000,0000,,2nd Lt. Dream of Valkyrie squadron,\Nthe item you ordered has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.20,0:11:15.77,intercom paging,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to base immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.77,0:11:20.61,intercom paging,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat: 2nd Lt. Dream of Valkyrie squadron,\Nthe item you ordered has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:18.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That broadcast...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:19.97,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a full launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:22.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakizaki! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:22.57,intercom paging,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to base immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:24.37,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,My steak...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:33.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Major Focker...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:37.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope you won't mind me\Ntaking up your Valkyrie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.16,0:11:41.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll work hard enough for the both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:03.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sempai...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.75,0:12:07.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Skull Squadron Unit One! Launching!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.42,0:12:08.05,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.03,0:12:20.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Skull Leader. Launch is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.77,0:12:22.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Skull Leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.44,0:12:28.07,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Lt. Ichijo will be flying\NMajor Focker's plane from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.04,0:12:30.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That boy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.39,0:12:45.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Skull Leader to planes Two and Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.37,0:12:47.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down in a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.81,0:12:49.81,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're dead, it's the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.88,0:12:51.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.52,0:12:52.65,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.67,0:12:58.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, men! Set electronic\Ncountermeasures to maximum!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.16,0:12:59.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Put on a good show!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:16.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.68,0:13:28.14,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Leader! I'm sure the\NMajor can rest in peace now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.15,0:13:33.12,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He just told you not to let your\Nguard down, remember?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.81,0:13:34.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:45.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,ECM level is 108.\NWe can proceed at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.35,0:13:49.75,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! All ships, descend to the surface!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:58.17,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's strange!\NLong-range radar signals are weakening!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:01.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,ECM, huh? So reinforcements are coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:03.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Put the new barrier system on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.00,0:14:05.70,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Have it ready inside of ten minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.93,0:14:09.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But Captain, if we put up a barrier we\Nwon't be able to fire our weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.69,0:14:13.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}All Valkyrie units, be ready for\Na second enemy wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.64,0:14:13.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We've finally found a place that\Nwill take in our civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.50,0:14:15.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Protecting the people\Ntakes top priority now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:16.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:19.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier system, stand by!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.61,0:14:29.61,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Flight Commander Milia, are you really\Ngoing aboard the miclone ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.61,0:14:30.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:34.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Lap'Lamiz seemed quite\Ndepressed about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:35.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.86,0:14:38.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Kamujin and his men run wild,\Nshe won't try to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:40.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:41.97,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:50.44,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill-'Em-All to Magdomilla.\NHow are things on your end?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.89,0:14:54.32,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Magdomilla here. We're near the\Nsurface, according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.43,0:14:57.05,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! All ships, advance on the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.27,0:14:59.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't fire until I get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:01.17,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.80,0:15:18.25,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the large-scale battleships!\NWhere did they come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.40,0:15:19.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Battleships?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.91,0:15:21.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Rapid barrier deployment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.13,0:15:24.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier system, rapid deployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:28.51,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier system, rapid deployment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:32.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier energy is increasing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:34.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Omni-Directional Barrier\Nhas been activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.00,0:15:41.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting an unusual energy reading\Nfrom around the enemy ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.88,0:15:43.35,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So what? Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.56,0:15:56.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All rounds, direct hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.09,0:15:57.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we destroy them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.47,0:16:01.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.10,0:16:07.06,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The barrier has been successfully deployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.02,0:16:10.52,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.76,0:16:13.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It deflected that huge attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.37,0:16:15.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be nice if it made the\Nenemy give up, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.17,0:16:18.11,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Energy absorption index: 95%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:19.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Deflection index: 3.3%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.82,0:16:23.26,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like that sphere thing\Ndeflected our attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:24.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.76,0:16:26.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? Blast them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.91,0:16:42.37,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy ships have entered the yellow\Nzone and are still closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.01,0:16:45.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So they aren't holding back\Nat all this time, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:49.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we ask UN Forces High\NCommand for assistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.25,0:16:50.27,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:53.66,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If High Command had any intention of intercepting\Nthe attack they would have done so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.92,0:16:57.85,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because you pressed the issue\Nof the civilians, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.92,0:16:59.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.78,0:17:01.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because if they tried to\Ntake on those large battleships
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.97,0:17:05.77,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and something went wrong, the Earth's\Nsurface would be badly damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.57,0:17:13.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier control to bridge.\NThe barrier system is unstable!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.75,0:17:14.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.60,0:17:15.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:22.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy may be serious this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.11,0:17:25.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to hit those battleships while\Nthe barrier's still holding!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.64,0:17:28.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're really serious,\Nwe may not stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:33.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Lt. Ichijo! Major Focker never whined\Nlike that in the middle of a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.17,0:17:37.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.63,0:17:40.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Max! Kakizaki! You heard the lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:43.57,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit the battleship at point\NAR-1181. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:47.25,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, if the Macross is\Ndestroyed, it's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:49.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, Leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.02,0:17:52.11,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Then try your hardest\Nnot to get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.56,0:17:54.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.74,0:18:20.87,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the enemy ship\Nhas just about had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.54,0:18:24.06,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Victory is now assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.19,0:18:31.66,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Output is falling in barrier generators 4 and 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.73,0:18:33.30,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Switch to subsystems!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.35,0:18:34.27,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:37.59,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a problem with the\Nfield-stabilization circuits!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:37.95,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,, {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}Converter 7 has exceeded limits!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.33,0:18:41.52,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Valkyrie Windsor Squadron\Nhas been wiped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:42.77,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,, {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}Emergency personnel, begin repair operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:43.56,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy fleet has entered the red zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.95,0:18:45.85,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They are continuing their attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.40,0:18:51.34,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting abnormalities\Nin the barrier system!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.41,0:18:54.03,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All personnel, evacuate immediately!\NEvacuate immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.89,0:19:02.62,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.28,0:19:04.85,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, all Valkyrie teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.39,0:19:07.56,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw immediately and get\Nas far away as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:09.78,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat, withdraw immediately and\Nget as far away as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.43,0:19:11.43,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.71,0:19:14.93,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The barrier is about to explode!\NGet away from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.07,0:19:16.69,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But what about the Macross?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.54,0:19:20.84,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:40.19,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Climb! Climb!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.81,0:19:45.94,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakizaki, don't fall behind! Kakizaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.46,0:19:49.09,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good! Leader, I'm not gonna make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:54.26,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,KAKIZAKI!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.99,0:20:17.85,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All blocks, damage reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.43,0:20:17.80,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}Rescue teams to barrier control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.92,0:20:19.96,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All the enemy ships appear to\Nhave been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.00,0:20:23.66,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the surface has been devastated\Nto a radius of at least 50 kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.32,0:20:28.77,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And only the Macross survived,\Nbecause we were at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.16,0:20:33.12,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, the Ontario Autonomous Region\Nis sending us an emergency message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:35.84,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.98,0:20:37.67,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to read what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.84,0:20:47.65,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The energy sustaining the barrier blasted\Noutward all at once and the surface was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.12,0:20:53.75,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ontario Autonomous Region has\Nrefused to take in the civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.53,0:20:58.09,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We lost Kakizaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.60,0:20:59.89,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:04.85,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least the Macross...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.67,0:21:08.80,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,At least the people aboard\Nthe Macross survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:16.51,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's Minmay's prognosis?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.61,0:21:17.91,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Will she recover?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.31,0:21:21.44,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaifun, as Minmay's cousin, as well\Nas her co-star in the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.53,0:21:23.51,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,we'd like you to give us a comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.56,0:21:27.43,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I... am highly doubtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:32.02,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The fighting thus far has already\Ncost us many precious lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.23,0:21:35.96,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and now rumor has it that the surface\Nhas been severely damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.96,0:21:38.29,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And does that have something to do\Nwith Minmay's hospitalization?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.53,0:21:39.86,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.09,0:21:42.73,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Even during a media blackout,\Nthey're reporting celebrity news?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.82,0:21:44.11,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaifun...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.14,0:21:47.46,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I simply fail to understand how in\Nthis time of great misfortune
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.51,0:21:50.24,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,you could be chasing after an actress who\Nmerely collapsed from overwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:54.85,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you be coming up with a way to get\Nthe military to put an end to the fighting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.97,0:21:57.58,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He says they should stop fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.88,0:22:00.15,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(362,395)} {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}It is my wish that you take steps\Nto put an end this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.70,0:22:02.52,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But that would deny the very thing that\Ngives life purpose! It's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:03.28,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,, {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}War creates nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:06.47,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But... I kind of understand how he feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.53,0:22:07.13,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,, {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}War results in just one thing,\Nand that is destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:11.21,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to remove ourselves from this\Nsenseless conflict right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.24,0:22:13.57,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the ones risking our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.39,0:22:19.16,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(358,409)} {\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}It is the only way to a lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.71,0:22:18.11,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(355,460)}Sometimes there are things you just can't\Nquit, no matter now much you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:23.27,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Ichijo, you have a call on phone three.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:29.50,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.58,0:22:32.09,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hikaru? I finally tracked you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:33.56,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.56,0:22:36.86,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what? I collapsed!\NBut I was just a little overworked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.30,0:22:40.40,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They've got me recuperating here\Nat Central Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:42.29,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been so busy lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.29,0:22:44.45,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only kind of time when\NI can take things easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.44,0:22:47.84,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're free, could you come over?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.49,0:22:51.55,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaifun still hasn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.10,0:22:58.40,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it doesn't have to be a big deal.\NJust stop by for a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.96,0:23:00.89,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why are you so quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.89,0:23:03.38,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to see you when you\Nwere hurt, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:08.36,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's Hikaru's problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.39,0:23:09.76,*Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He's so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.10,0:23:34.97,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(333,455)}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.10,0:23:34.97,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(73,108)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.94,0:23:39.07,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Britai has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.12,0:23:42.92,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,The three Zentradi spies make their\Nescape from the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.00,0:23:48.77,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Their destination is the great fleet led by Britai,\Nwhich consists of over 1,000 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.60,0:23:54.23,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle of all this, the Macross\Nis ordered back into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:58.10,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Super Dimension\NFortress Macross:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.19,0:24:00.31,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,"PARADISE LOST"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.58,0:24:02.07,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(66,136)}PARADISE LOST
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.33,0:24:22.99,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't follow it anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.34,0:24:29.74,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The shadow you cast as you run away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.89,0:24:36.19,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,We all keep running until the end
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.19,0:24:43.66,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still can't see the goal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.78,0:24:50.15,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us after today?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.96,0:24:56.52,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us beyond tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.78,0:25:04.05,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I keep running toward
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.33,0:25:15.57,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The light that shines so far away
